The paper proposes a novel hashing learning framework for cross-modal retrieval, which involves learning a common subspace and discriminative hashing codes. This suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves classifier learning and subspace learning, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves statistical features, which could suggest a potential fit for the statistical learning (cs.SI) sub-category.
